            "content": "---\ntitle: \"fix: Route checkpoints to correct nested subrepo instead of parent repo\"\ntype: fix\nstatus: active\ndate: 2026-04-01\n---\n\n# fix: Route checkpoints to correct nested subrepo instead of parent repo\n\n## Overview\n\nWhen an AI agent (Cursor, Claude Code, Codex, etc.) is launched from a parent git repo that contains nested subrepos (independent git repos as subdirectories), checkpoints are incorrectly written to the parent repo's `.git/ai/working_logs/` instead of the subrepo's. This causes `git-ai status` in the subrepo to show all agent edits as \"human\".\n\n## Problem Frame\n\n**Repo layout:**\n```\nparentRepo/\n  .git/\n  src/\n  subrepo-1/\n    .git/\n    src/\n  subrepo-2/\n    .git/\n    src/\n```\n\n**What happens now:**\n1. User launches Cursor (or any agent) in `parentRepo/`\n2. Agent edits `parentRepo/subrepo-1/src/foo.ts`\n3. Agent hook fires: `git-ai checkpoint cursor --hook-input stdin`\n4. Handler extracts CWD = `parentRepo/` from hook payload\n5. `find_repository_in_path(\"parentRepo/\")` succeeds -- finds parentRepo's `.git/`\n6. `needs_file_based_repo_detection = false` (line 658 of `git_ai_handlers.rs`)\n7. Checkpoint is written to `parentRepo/.git/ai/working_logs/`\n8. `git-ai status` in `subrepo-1/` reads `subrepo-1/.git/ai/working_logs/` -- finds nothing -- reports \"human\"\n\n**What should happen:**\n- The handler should detect that the edited file belongs to `subrepo-1` (which has its own `.git/`), and route the checkpoint to `subrepo-1/.git/ai/working_logs/`.\n\n**All agents are affected.** Every preset returns `repo_working_dir` based on the agent's CWD or workspace root, not based on where the edited files actually live. The bug is in the handler's decision logic, not in individual presets.\n\n## Requirements Trace\n\n- R1. When an agent's CWD is a parent repo containing nested subrepos, checkpoints for subrepo files must be written to the subrepo's `.git/ai/`, not the parent's.\n- R2. The fix must