n- `create_unique_workspace()` for temp directories\n\n**Test scenarios:**\n\nHappy path:\n- Claude preset: CWD is parentRepo, PostToolUse edits file in nested subrepo -> AI attribution in subrepo\n- Claude preset: CWD is parentRepo, PreToolUse + PostToolUse cycle for file in nested subrepo -> correct attribution\n\nEdge case:\n- Claude preset: CWD is parentRepo, edits file that is in parentRepo (not in any subrepo) -> normal attribution in parentRepo (no regression)\n\n**Verification:**\n- New tests pass\n- Scenario 6 tests still pass unchanged\n\n- [ ] **Unit 3: Add `mock_ai` integration tests for nested repo checkpoint routing**\n\n**Goal:** Verify the core routing fix works with `mock_ai` preset (used by most existing cross-repo tests) for thorough coverage of the nested-repo layout.\n\n**Requirements:** R1, R3, R4\n\n**Dependencies:** Unit 1\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `tests/integration/cross_repo_cwd_attribution.rs`\n\n**Approach:**\n\nAdd scenarios using `mock_ai` with nested repo layout:\n- Single file in nested subrepo\n- Multiple files across multiple nested subrepos\n- Mixed: some files in parent repo, some in nested subrepo\n- Blame verification for nested subrepo files\n\nThese use `checkpoint mock_ai <absolute-file-paths>` from the parent repo's CWD.\n\n**Patterns to follow:**\n- Scenarios 1-5 test structure\n- `git_ai_from_working_dir()` helper\n\n**Test scenarios:**\n\nHappy path:\n- CWD is parentRepo, `checkpoint mock_ai subrepo-1/file.txt` -> AI attestations in subrepo-1\n- CWD is parentRepo, `checkpoint mock_ai subrepo-1/a.txt subrepo-2/b.txt` -> attestations in both subrepos\n- CWD is parentRepo, `checkpoint mock_ai src/parent.txt subrepo-1/file.txt` -> attestations in parentRepo AND subrepo-1\n\nEdge case:\n- CWD is parentRepo, file in subrepo uses relative path (`subrepo-1/src/foo.ts` not absolute) -> correctly resolved\n\nIntegration:\n- Blame shows correct AI/human attribution for nested subrepo file after cross-repo checkpoint\n\n**Verification:**\n- All new tests pass\n- All existing tests pass\n\n## System-Wide Impact\n\n- **Interaction graph:** The fix is localized to the checkpoint handler's repo-routing decision. Downstream components (`run_checkpoint_via_daemon_or_local`, working log writer, post-commit hook, status, blame) are not changed.\n- **Error propagation:** If `find_repository_for_file()` fails for a specific file during the nested-repo check, it should not block other files. The existing `group_files_by_repository()` already handles this via its orphan files list.\n- **State lifecycle risks:** None. Working logs are append-only per base-commit. Routing to a different repo just means writing to a different `.git/ai/` directory.\n- **API surface parity:** No API changes. All agent presets benefit from the fix without modification.\n- **Integration coverage:** Covered by Unit 2 (Claude preset) and Unit 3 (mock_ai) tests.\n- **Unchanged invariants:** The multi-repo processing path (lines 660-841) is not modified, only entered more often. The single-repo path is unchanged for cases where all files genuinely belong to the CWD repo.\n\n## Risks & Dependencies\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Performance: calling `find_repository_for_file()` for every edited file adds overhead | Only called when explicit file paths are provided. Typically 1-5 files per checkpoint. The function is a directory walk, not a git command -- negligible cost. Can short-circuit after finding the first file in a different repo. |\n| False positive: a file path that happens to traverse through a nested `.git/` that isn't a real subrepo | `find_repository_for_file()` already handles submodules (skips them). Independent nested repos with `.git/` directories are genuine repos by definition. |\n| Regression in existing cross-repo tests | All existing tests use CWD that is either a non-git directory or a sibling repo. The new check only activates when CWD IS a git repo but files belong to a NESTED repo. No existing behavior changes. |\n\n## Sources & References\n\n- Related code: `src/commands/git_ai_handlers.rs:637-900`, `src/git/repository.rs:2894-3008`\n- Related tests: `tests/integration/cross_repo_cwd_attribution.rs`\n- Related issue: #871 (cross-repo CWD attribution for sibling repos -- already fixed, this extends to nested repos)\n",
