ies (real nested repos), not `.git` files (which indicate submodules). This mirrors the existing logic in `find_repository_for_file`.\n\n- **Q: What if the agent doesn't provide file paths in the hook payload?** The `external_files` filter only runs when file paths exist. No file paths = no `path_is_in_workdir` calls = no behavior change. The existing fallback is fine.\n\n- **Q: Performance of checking intermediate directories?** The check only adds a directory walk between workdir and file path -- typically 1-3 intermediate directories. Each check is a single `Path::join(\".git\").exists()` call. Negligible cost.\n\n- **Q: Could this break the `path_is_in_workdir` unit test?** The existing test at `git_repository_comprehensive.rs:148` tests \"inside\" vs \"outside\" paths. Nested subrepo paths are a new case not covered. A new test case must be added.\n\n## Implementation Units\n\n- [ ] **Unit 1: Fix `path_is_in_workdir` to detect nested subrepo boundaries**\n\n**Goal:** Make `path_is_in_workdir` return `false` for files inside nested independent git repos within the workdir. This makes the existing `external_files` mechanism correctly route subrepo files.\n\n**Requirements:** R1, R2, R3\n\n**Dependencies:** None\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/git/repository.rs` (function `path_is_in_workdir`)\n- Modify: `tests/integration/git_repository_comprehensive.rs` (add nested repo test case)\n\n**Approach:**\n\nAfter the existing `starts_with` check returns `true`, add a second check: walk the intermediate path segments between the workdir and the file path. For each intermediate directory, check if it contains a `.git/` directory (not a `.git` file -- files indicate submodules which should remain transparent to the parent repo).\n\nIf an intervening `.git/` directory is found, return `false` -- the file belongs to a nested repo, not this repo.\n\nPseudocode:\n```\nfn path_is_in_workdir(&self, path: &Path) -> bool {\n    // existing starts_with check\n    if !canonical_path.