ectory of parentRepo with its own `git init`\n- Use `git_ai_from_working_dir(&parent_path, &[\"checkpoint\", \"mock_ai\", abs_subrepo_file])`\n- Verify working logs exist in subrepo-1, not parentRepo\n- Commit in subrepo-1 and verify AI attestations\n\n**Patterns to follow:**\n- Scenario 4 structure (`test_cwd_is_parent_dir_above_repos_single_repo`) -- closest pattern but with nested repos instead of sibling repos\n- `TestRepo::new_at_path()` for creating repos at specific locations\n\n**Test scenarios:**\n\nHappy path:\n- CWD is parentRepo, single file in nested subrepo -> working log + attestations in subrepo\n- CWD is parentRepo, files in two nested subrepos -> attestations in both subrepos\n- CWD is parentRepo, mixed: file in parentRepo + file in subrepo -> attestations in both repos separately\n\nEdge case:\n- CWD is parentRepo, file in subrepo at deeply nested path -> attestations in subrepo\n\nIntegration:\n- Blame verification: human lines in subrepo stay human, AI-appended lines show as AI\n\n**Verification:**\n- New tests pass; all existing `cross_repo_cwd_attribution` tests pass\n- Working log assertions confirm data is in subrepo's `.git/ai/`, not parent's\n\n- [ ] **Unit 3: Add nested-repo integration tests with Claude preset**\n\n**Goal:** Verify the fix works with a real agent preset (Claude) using structured hook input, analogous to scenario 6 (issue #871) but with nested repos.\n\n**Requirements:** R2, R5\n\n**Dependencies:** Unit 1\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `tests/integration/cross_repo_cwd_attribution.rs`\n\n**Approach:**\n\nAdd scenario 7 mirroring scenario 6 structure:\n- Create parentRepo with `git init`\n- Create subrepo as subdirectory of parentRepo with its own `git init`\n- Build Claude `PostToolUse` hook JSON with `cwd` = parentRepo, `file_path` = absolute path in subrepo\n- Run checkpoint, commit in subrepo, verify attestations and prompts are non-empty\n\nAlso add `PreToolUse` + `PostToolUse` cycle test.\n\n**Patterns to follow:**\n- `tes